":false,"content":"100 g blanched almonds"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1000 g whole milk"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"250 g caster sugar"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 lemon, thin peelings of skin only"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 vanilla pod and scraped out seeds"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g risotto rice"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g candied mixed peel"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"5 medium eggs, beaten"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 pinch fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g Amaretto or other almond liqueur"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1036 kJ \/ 246 kcal","7 g","31.5 g","8.5 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["This comforting cake dates back to the early 20th century when peasant women in the Emilia-Romagna region of Italy would help cultivate the famous short-grain Arborio rice. Once the harvest was over, the families were left with an abundance of rice, so the women experimented by creating different sweet and savoury dishes. <i>Torta di riso<\/i> is one such creation and is made when the plump grains of rice are slowly cooked in milk and spices before being baked until golden.","To check the temperature of the mixture as it cools, return the mixing bowl to position and wait a few seconds for the temperature to display on the Thermomix.","To allow the mixture to cool faster, transfer to a ceramic or glass bowl and leave to cool, then return to mixing bowl to continue the recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","8h 30m","16 portions"]}